-- England Leads Pakistan by 70 After First Innings in Second Cricket Test
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2012-01-27T09:01:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/england-leads-pakistan-by-70-after-first-innings-in-second-cricket-test.html
England  leads Pakistan by 70 runs
after being bowled out for 327 runs in its first innings in
their second cricket Test.  Stuart Broad was unbeaten on 58 to help push England from
207-5 at the start of the third day. It lost four late wickets
yesterday and trailed by 50 runs in  Abu Dhabi .  Alastair Cook and Jonathan Trott combined for 139 runs,
with Cook leading England with 94 runs.  Saeed Ajmal, who took 10 wickets in the first Test,
continued to hurt England, finishing the innings 4-108.  Pakistan, which leads the series 1-0 after a 10-wicket win
in the opening match, won the toss and elected to bat. Misbah-
ul-Haqâ€™s 84 runs pushed Pakistan to 257 all out. Abdur Rehman,
Ajmal and Junaid Khan were out for no runs, while  Umar Gul 
finished unbeaten but failed to score.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
